# Zunera

> Associate Professor, University of Warwick. Researching policing, security and social order in the Global South.

Zunera is an Associate Professor at the University of Warwick working on criminology, law and socio-legal studies. Her research focuses on law enforcement, digitalisation, cybercrime, surveillance and urban (in)security, with a particular emphasis on South Asia and the Global South. She studied at SOAS and King's College London, and held postdoctoral and teaching positions at UCL.

Research interests: Policing, Urban (in)security, Surveillance, Cybercrime, Digitalisation, Postcolonial criminology, South Asia.

Affiliations:
- Co-coordinator, Urban Violence Research Network (https://urbanviolence.org/)
- Non-resident Scholar, Carnegie Endowment for International Peace (https://carnegieendowment.org/)
- Affiliate, Institute for Global City Policing, UCL (https://www.ucl.ac.uk/jill-dando-institute/people/zoha-waseem)

